      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/71/2",
      "text": [
        " اَلرَّجُلِ اَلَّذِي يُسْلِمُ فَيُرِيدُ أَنْ يَخْتَتِنَ وَ قَدْ حَضَرَ اَلْحَجُّ أَ يَحُجُّ أَوْ يَخْتَتِنُ قَالَ «لاَ يَحُجُّ حَتَّى يَخْتَتِنَ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2815 - Ibn Maskan narrated from Ibrahim ibn Maymun, who reported from Imam Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who converts to Islam and intends to undergo circumcision while the time for Hajj has arrived.\nHe asked: Should he perform Hajj or undergo circumcision?\nImam (as) replied: \"He should not perform Hajj until he is circumcised.\""
        ]
      }
    },
